      "writtenOn": "2020-05-06T14:18:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, I think my comments here are related; I don\u0027t love how much this code knows about the structure of the checkouts, how to get the hash, etc.  Writing the new revision ID to a file is very similar to what other rollers do in their normal flow, the only difference being that this file has some structure.  I think I\u0027d prefer to either integrate this into version_file_common by adding a Template field to the VersionFileConfig struct (https://skia.googlesource.com/buildbot/+/master/autoroll/go/repo_manager/common/version_file_common/version_file_common.go#13), or add something similar to the AndroidRepoManagerConfig.\n\nOut of curiosity, where does the structure of this file come from?  Is it intended to be parsed?  If so, is there a proto definition we can use to write it rather than a hard-coded template?",
